
CSS SELECTORS

/* select any span that has a parent div */
div span{
  background-color: orange;
  
  div > span {
    background-color: pink;;
    }
    
    section ~ span (sibling selector) general sibling selector
      will select any sibling span of a selector
      
    section + span ( only span directly afer) adjacent sibling selector
      will select any sibling span directly after selector
    
first-child (psuedo selector)
nth-child(x) 

hover
changes action when cursor hovers over element

before and after
ex. 

ul::before {
  content: 'ul::before';
}
 ul::after {
   content: 'ul::after';
 }
 
 CSS LAYOUT
 
 margin: 5rem, auto, 2rem, auto 
 (example...works clockwise starting at the top
 top, right, bottom, left)
 
 ex.
 border-width:
 border-style:
 border-color: (has a default, and will show up alone. others will not)
 
 borders: 5px, 100px, 5px, 100px. same applies. top, right,bottom, left
 or just submit first two numbers, as the bottom and left will mirror, top and right
 
